h: variant of   Barrett  ."]},{"name":"Barratt","meanings":["English: variant of   Barrett  ."]}]},{"name":"Jonathan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Johnathan","meanings":["Respelling of   Jonathan  , as if a combination of   John   and   Nathan ."]},{"name":"Jonathon","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonathen","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Johnathon","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: respelled form of   Jonathan  , influenced by   John ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jonathan Barrett was born in 1475, in Wiltshire, England, his father, John Barrett, was 20 and his mother, Alice Kessell, was 15. He had at least 1 daughter. He died after 1498, in Bratton, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1475–after 1498":"1475–pärast 1498","1475–1498":"1475–1498","1482–Male":"1482–Surnud","1501–Female":"1501–Surnud","1456–1490":"1456–1490","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1501":"1501","about 1490":"umbes 1490","1456":"1456","1498":"1498","1475":"1475","1460":"1460","1482":"1482","1490":"1490","after 1498":"pärast 1498","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","England":"England","Bratton, Wiltshire, England":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1475–after 1498":"1475–1498 jälkeen","1475–1498":"1475–1498","1482–Male":"1482–Kuollut","1501–Female":"1501–Kuollut","1456–1490":"1456–1490","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1501":"1501","about 1490":"noin 1490","1456":"1456","1498":"1498","1475":"1475","1460":"1460","1482":"1482","1490":"1490","after 1498":"1498 jälkeen","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","England":"England","Bratton, Wiltshire, England":"Bratton, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1475–after 1498":"1475–après 1498","1475–1498":"1475–1498","1482–Male":"1482–Décédé","1501–Female":"1501–Décédée","1456–1490":"1456–1490","1460–Female":"1460–Décédée","1501":"1501","ab